title: Thunderbird 140.0.1 is resource hungry
content:
I am experiencing a severe problem with Thunderbird. There are several symptoms: 1) The CPU utilization of Thunderbird is typically 13-19%. 2) Thunderbird declares that it was able to send a message and to save it, but that it experienced difficulty when running filters. 3) Thunderbird is unable to compact a folder. The message received is: 

   The folder 'Inbox on william.atwood@concordia.ca' could not be compacted because writing to folder failed.  Verify that you have enough disk space, and that you have write privileges to the file system, then try again.

4) Thunderbird occasionally gives the following error message: Your message was sent but a copy was not placed in your sent folder (Sent) due to network or file access errors. You can retry or save the message locally to Local Folders/Sent-william.atwood@concordia.ca.

These are the symptoms that I see today. Over the longer term, I saw the following:

1) Thunderbird started to behave strangely several weeks ago. It somehow lost track of what messages it had downloaded, so it started downloading all of the message headers in my inboxes (and other folders). (I have six email accounts that I monitor.)

2) Since all of my accounts are IMAP accounts, with the messages stored on the server, I tried replacing the Thunderbird profile with a copy that I had previously backed up. This seemed to solve the problem for a short time. However, the symptoms soon re-appeared, including high CPU utilization, inability to compact folders, and difficulty running filters.

3) At the suggestion of my employer's help desk, I removed and re-installed Thunderbird. This found the existing Thunderbird profile, and everything seemed to work just fine for a few days. Then, suddenly, everything went haywire, and Thunderbird started re-loading all of the message headers for *all* of my folders (and for all of the accounts), and complaining about inability to run filters or compact folders.

Finally, Thunderbird crashed today. I added notes to the crash report, giving some of the details above. After it restarted, it crashed again. I finally ended up restarting my computer.

Thunderbird version 140.0.1 Windows 11 Edition Windows 11 Enterprise Version 24H2 Installed on ‎2025-‎04-‎30 OS build 26100.4349 Experience Windows Feature Experience Pack 1000.26100.107.0

What can I do to mitigate this problem? It is very difficult to use Thunderbird when it acts like this.

Bill Atwood
creator: williamatwood41

title: Eeste gestor, no me detecta los correos SPAM.
content: 21/07/2025. Hola - Disculpe señor. No soy muy ducho - Le pido perdón. Abro un nuevo hilo . . . - Está bien ? - - - Antecedentes : Mi primera pregunta 06/04/2025. Tengo este problemita : De vez en cuando recibo correos SPAM y este gestor no me los detecta. Como debería configurar, para que cuando me llegue un correo SPAM, me avise y lo detecte ? Aclaro, que solamente me entero cuando voy a mi correo en la web, y ahí sí, lo veo. Muchas gracias - Saludos cordiales. - - - Su contestación 6/4/2025. Hola, Adjunte una captura de la configuración de la cuenta "opciones de correo basura" (su versión puede tener un nombre diferente pero similar a este), en este menú tiene una explicación de su funcionamiento, donde se refiere a "entrenar" estud deberá en un principio marcar que correos son spam. Ademas puede agregar una funcionalidad ms antispam marcando la opción de "Confiar en los encabezados de basura de..", estos son servidores de detección de spam. Saludos - - - Su respuesta 7/4/2025. Hola, Están correctas esas configuraciones, pero en la última captura puede activar también "Activar el registro del filtro adaptativo de correo basura" PD: Cuando escribe un correo lo hace también todo en mayúscula ? Saludos - - Su última respuesta 7/4/2025 Modificadas por GerardoPcp 04 de abril de 2025, 9:06:2 Para agregar o quitar carpeta se hace con la suscripción de la cuenta - (clic botón derecho del mouse sobre la cuenta de correo) - en las cuentas IMAP, entiendo que su cuenta es IMAP y según me comento esta opción no aparece en la cuenta de yahoo. Otras opciones : Que la carpeta "correos no deseados" se haya movido sin querer a otra carpeta, habría que revisar el resto de las carpetas. Saludos - - - 20/07/2025. Hola, Si me responde en otra consulta se me hace difícil seguir el hilo del problema ya que no veo lo que le respondí antes. Para agregar o quitar carpeta se hace con la suscripción de la cuenta (clic botón derecho del mouse sobre la cuenta de correo) en las cuentas IMAP, su cuenta es IMAP ? Según me comento esta opción no aparece en su cuenta de yahoo, sin embargo, agregue mi cuenta de Yahoo al Thunderbird y si tiene la opción de suscripción, Otras opciones : Que la carpeta "correos no deseado" se haya movido sin querer a otra carpeta, habría que revisar el resto de las carpetas. Si su cuenta es POP3 lamentablemente ya he dejado de usar hace muchos años las cuentas POP3 y hay muy pocos usuarios que todavía siguen usándola. - - - 21/07/2025. Estoy usando POP3 y no IMAP. Por favor - no lo tome a mal - donde tengo el error entonces ? Le adjunto 5 capturas de pantalla. Gracias.!!!

title: Thunderbird displaying images problem
content: Hello, I've come across a rather strange problem. I have a phplist mailing list (on domain1). When sending emails, I usually also add an image (as a link to the image). Since the beginning of June, however, I've noticed that Thunderbird doesn't display the images added in this way. Instead of the image, it displays an empty frame (a completely empty frame without any tags). Even if "Allow remote content in messages" is checked in the settings. Other email clients (outlook, gmail, roundcube) have no problems and display images without any problems. However, if I put the image on another domain (domain2) and put a link to this image in the email, Thunderbird also displays it. So: it doesn't display the image from domain1, where I have the mailing list, but it displays the same image from domain2 (in the same email from the same mailing list from domain1). Is it possible that Thunderbird is blocking the display of images from a certain domain?

title: Upgrading to 140.0.1 (esr) 64bits broke my profile
content:
Hi,

Just upgraded to 140.0.1 and when I restarted Thunderbird it asked that I create a new profile, as if it was the first time I used it. I checked in %APPDATA%/Thunderbird/Profiles, I have 2 folders, one ends with .default (47 b), the other one, ends with .default-release (around 7Gb). I've tried messing a bit with the profiles.ini and the install.ini files but it didn't change anything appart from creating other 47b folders when restarting Thunderbird. So I'm back to the original files but I'm stuck. When I open the about:profiles page, the .default-release one does appear at the top and seems to be the default one, yet nothing shows up in the usual window.

What should I do?

Thanks a lot

title: Emails deleted from my Thunderbird folders
content:
I use Mozilla Thunderbird to import and manage my GMail account. It has always worked very well. I have a large number of folders in the Mozilla Thunderbird program (parallels those in Gmail) and, frankly, use it as a filing system. This morning when I went into Thunderbird I discovered that the emails stored in the folders were all gone, except for those from about May 14th 2025 or more recent than that. I have lost a huge amount of information that was kept in those emails in folders. I checked the ALL MAIL folder in Thunderbird and those emails are gone from that folder as well. I followed the instructions Google gave me to check Trash and Spam folders and try to repair the folder but this is doing nothing. I also went directly to GMail and these same emails have been deleted from those folders as well. I have years of important information stored in emails in the Mozilla Thunderbird account and want to know why they disappeared and, most importantly, how they can be retrieved and I can orpevent this happening againin the future! Thanks you for helping solve this problem. I cannot stress enough how much of my professional and personal life is captured in the emails I had stored in the Thunderbird folders so anything you can do to help will be greatly appreciated. Thanks,

Harvey Weingarten
creator: hpweingarten

title: Upgraded to Thunderbird 140 and AT&T email not syncing
content:
I upgraded to Thunderbird 140.0.1esr (64 bit) and 1 of the 4 email accounts has stopped syncing.

The one that stopped syncing is AT&T / Yahoo email via imap inbound and smtp outbound. It was working on the 128 release but as soon as I updated it stopped syncing.

I can still get email to/from the other 3 accounts, it still works on my phone and on my laptop with Thunderbird 128.12.0esr (32-bit) it is still working OK.

I have double checked account info and passwords and no issues that I can see.

My next thought is to downgrade back to 128 unless someone knows of a fix.
creator: josephd.henderson

title: Messages moved to spam folder on server not deleting per filter
content: I have a filter for a particularly frequent spam FROM: address. The filter is set to act when anything in the FROM contains the spam address "onmicrosoft.com". When it locates such, the filter marks the message read, and then moves the message to TRASH on my main account. The problem is, I think, that these messages are caught by my server-side spam filter and it moves the messages to the Spam folder. And the filter can't see them there I guess. A lot of what gets marked spam by the server is wrong, and I want those in the spam filter so I can go on the server and mark them NOT SPAM. So I want these I know are spam to go to the trash, and I'll just delete them unread. Is there a way to point the filters at the spam folder and not just the inbox?

It seemed too complicated to resolve, so I've just been forcing TB to quit when I get the "Thunderbird is not responding" message. I've done that hundreds of times since November, 2023.

Now I want to use a newer computer and thought I would install the latest version of TB. I wonder if I have corrupted my profile by all the force quits. Should I create a new profile and just start from scratch?

title: add certificate exceptions
content:
I'm basically trying to help and support others. Please re-enable the security exception popup for all necessary cases. We've tested it, and even in an installation where the exceptions were previously loaded, once removed, it's no longer possible to load the email again. We don't need more features—just that what used to work doesn't stop working.

Doing it manually on each installation is far too slow.

title: Email loss after clicking "Compact now"
content:
Thunderbird v. 115.10.1 (64-bit) Windows 10

Several months ago I experienced Inbox email loss whenever I clicked "Compact now" in the "Compact folders" dialog. After a couple of occurrences I trained myself to only click "Remind me later" thus avoiding the email loss. Today I goofed and clicked "Compact now". Many important opened and unopened emails disappeared from my Inbox as a result. I waited a while to make sure Compact folders had completed the operation but no lost emails reappeared. I shut down and relaunched Thunderbird but no lost emails reappeared. I don't know if any of my other folders have experienced this email loss.

My most recent backup will restore some of what was lost from my Inbox. But not the new unread emails.

What can I do to prevent this from happening again? Can I disable "Compact folders" completely so the problem never re-occurs?

I haven't upgraded to Thunderbird 116.0 because my backups are from v. 115.10.1 and I have experienced problems restoring Thunderbird with a previous versioned backup.

Thanks in advance for your advice.
creator: wherry
